summary: Peer from IC is assisting a customer, Vikram, with a product supply issue. The customer's wholesale shop is not being supplied with goods from Chennai, which is affecting their business. They used to get their supplies from a different distributor and are wondering why there have been changes. The customer would like to file a complaint regarding the issue as their shop, which is a big blessing, is not being properly supplied. The customer provides details of the problem and the name and address of their store. They also mention that the salesman no longer visits their shop. The customer is asked to file a complaint, and they provide contact information for Ashok. The call ends with the customer thanking Sampat.
speaker_a_summary: The customer, whose name is Ashok, calls IC to speak to a Telugu-speaking agent in order to register a complaint. They used to have regular visits from a salesman, but that has stopped. Ashok provides their store name, address, and email, as well as the name of the distributor, in order to raise the issue and hopefully have the salesman resume his visits.  The agent, Peer, takes down the information and promises to look into it, ending the call by telling Ashok that they will be in touch with him shortly.  The information provided by Ashok will be forwarded to the appropriate team in order to handle the complaint and resume the needed services as soon as possible.  The call ends.
speaker_b_summary: Namdu JP Nagar Bangalore is writing to complain about supply issues and disrespectful behaviour from Ivru Boyg Bandangella, their new distributor. Namdu says that they used to get supplies from Avr Chennai for four years, but now it has been changed and they are facing problems. Namdu says that they have not received supply for the past two months, and Ivru Boyg Bandangella does not supply correctly or on time. They ask to make a complaint to the President of Vijayanagar to change the Jayanagar distribute as they are facing issues with the new distributor. They ask for a supply code and also mention that they used to get supplies from Chennai which were better.
